  • Constructor Details

    • LogicCell

      public LogicCell(String name, HashSet<String> synapseNames, LinkedList<Activator> activators, byte[] cryptoKey)
      Allocates a new LogicCell object using specification sets.
      Parameters:
      name - The cell's name at runtime. This name should be unique across the entire cell system.
      synapseNames - The synapses this cell listens on and/or connects to.
      activators - The cell's activators.
      cryptoKey - The stimulus encryption key. Specify null to disable encryption using a user-specified key. If disabled, the stimuli will still be encrypted as part of NeuPaths protocol encryption.
